About the Team
The Cloud Infrastructure team, based in Singapore, is primarily responsible for the firm's infrastructure and technical architecture. Relying on the cloud-native environment, the PaaS team creates a simple and easy-to-use service hosting platform for developers, improving research and development efficiency whilst reducing service maintenance costs. PaaS comes from a service perspective, connecting developers with the cloud-native environment, shielding developers from the learning costs of Kubernetes, and providing functions such as service hosting, code release, capacity adjustment, as well as operation and maintenance governance. The Engineering Productivity Serverless team is committed to building industry-leading R&D Serverless solutions, including basic runtime, high-density deployment, universal deployment capabilities, commercialization solutions, etc.

Joining our department, you can look forward to growing and developing through ample opportunities in training and exposure. We look forward to your application! 

What you will be doing:
- Design and develop internal tooling, application engines serving billions of requests and the key component for PaaS;
- Design the organisation business-oriented architecture, and construct an efficient online/offline service hosting platform;
- Develop advanced intelligent data platform, and help client developers make decisions to optimize the user experience of our products;
- Provide solutions for internal product lines, and integrate with business-oriented frameworks;
- Improve the reliability of the system, and manage the challenges of scale and complexity;
- Introduce new server architecture, to manage extreme performance from hardware and handle large amounts of requests. 

Qualifications

 - Final year or recent graduate with a background in Software Development, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or a related technical discipline.
- Interest in computer science and internet technology with high proficiency in at least one programming language, including but not limited to Java, C, C++, Golang, Python, and PHP;
- Solid computer basic knowledge, in-depth understanding of data structure, algorithms, and operating system knowledge;
- Excellent ability for logical analysis and business logic abstraction;
- Excellent communication skills with a strong thirst for knowledge and a keen desire to learn;
- Experience in PaaS / Serverless / R&D platform projects is a plus.

